{
  "format_version": 3,
  "instrument": "groovebox",
  "doc": "A free-running synthesized step-sequenced beatmaker (V1.3 Toy 1). Three lanes \u2014 kick, snare, hat \u2014 each a 16-step boolean gate sequencer (gate_mode=Gate) feeding a one-voice Voicer that hosts the lane's drum-synth voice patch (kick-voice / snare-voice / hat-voice, built entirely from operators, no samples). One shared clock at division=4 makes a 16th-note grid; the pattern loops forever, instant sound, no transport. Every player-facing control is an interface input pipe: toggle steps with /kick_step1/in../kick_step16/in (and /snare_step*, /hat_step*); each step is boolean on/off. Ride tempo with /tempo/in, lane volumes with the /kick_vol/in /snare_vol/in /hat_vol/in knobs, sweep the whole kit with the /tone/in DJ-filter knob (0.5 rests neutral; below sweeps the lowpass closed, above thins into the highpass), and set the master level with the /volume/in knob (default 0.5 = -6 dB). The drum mix is glued by a saturator ahead of the master DJ filter; its /drive/in knob (1..30, rests at 3) rides the glue from barely-on warmth to full squash. Drums: kick = sine with a fast pitch-drop env; snare = noise + a tonal osc; hat = highpassed noise tick.",
  "resources": {
    "hat-voice": "voices/hat-voice.json",
    "kick-voice": "voices/kick-voice.json",
    "snare-voice": "voices/snare-voice.json"
  },
